<div class="content-data"><div id="list-content-mobile" class="hidden-md hidden-lg"></div><div class="lesson-tab" role="tabpanel"><ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist"><li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#about" aria-controls="about" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Course details</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#transcript" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Transcript</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#pattern" aria-controls="pattern" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Pattern</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#diploma" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Diploma</a></li><li role="presentation"><a class="faq-tab blank" href="#faq" aria-controls="faq" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">FAQs</a></li></ul><div class="tab-content"><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="about"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><div class="demo-slider"><h4 class="text-center">Garments you can make using this technology:</h4><div id="amazingcarousel-container"><div id="amazingcarousel" style="display:none"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-wrapper"><ul class="amazingcarousel-list"><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5737.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5737.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5840.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5840.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li></ul></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>The popularity of this model among brides is because it reflects almost all following fashion trends:</strong></p><ul><li>a delicate elastic top with embroidery;</li><li>a built-in bra or cut-off cups;</li><li>a tender silhouette of a lace dress;</li><li>an open back and a short lacing on air loops;</li><li>and a full detachable skirt with a train.</li></ul><p><strong>This course contains a lot of couture techniques. I will show you the following:</strong></p><ul><li>how to seamlessly cover the corset with lace;</li><li>how to join a lace folded skirt to a dress, so that you don’t have any extra thickness and the transition from a corset to a dress is smooth and invisible;</li><li>how to sew an elastic top between a face and a lining;</li><li>how to make a lining with built-in cups.</li></ul><p><strong>The special feature of the course is tambour (luneville) sequin embroidery.</strong></p><p>The process of cutting, sewing and decoration of a garment from scratch to final operations is described and illustrated in detail.<br> All necessary patterns and bonuses (for printing) are attached as follows:</p><ul><li>2 tables for AUTOMATIC pattern adjustments calculation for all patterns of this course;</li><li>patterns of a corset face and a corset lining;</li><li>patterns of decorative details.</li></ul><div><p><strong>The aim of the course</strong>&nbsp;is my great desire to teach the techniques of making such dresses. All the techniques can be used in various combinations, so that you can sew different models of evening, cocktail, prom and wedding dresses.</p><p><strong>The course is useful</strong>&nbsp;both to beginners as well as to experienced professionals in making wedding and evening dresses. It can be handy for dressmaking atelier personnel as a professional development training.</p></div><div></div><div><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;5h 00m</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-47-internal-part-of-padding/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-47-internal-part-of-padding/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-12-05T21:43:38+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-12-05T21:43:38+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 47. Internal part of padding."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 47. Internal part of padding."><meta itemprop="description" content="At this tutorial I will teach you how to finish internal gore of padding and attach it to voluminous piece."><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Dress with Detachable Full Skirt. Part 2."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding dress with detachable full skirt. part 2., video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h2>Tutorial 47. Internal part of padding.</h2><p><strong>At this tutorial I will teach you how to finish internal gore of padding and attach it to voluminous piece.&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>According to gore pattern, </strong>which I made using a mock-up method or draping method, I cut it from synthetic thick and semi-transparent non-fraying fabric. Additionally I drafted a 3.5 cm wide belt, which length is equal to length of the upper cut of the gore.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Two vertical and one lower cut of gore will be sewn with thin pencil-edge, using a 1.2 cm wide bias tape. All cuts of gore are without seam allowances.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I attach the bias tape along the first vertical cut of gore.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I attach bias tape along the second vertical cut. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I sew the pencil-edge to the vertical cut of gore. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image022.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I sew the pencil-edge to the second vertical cut of gore. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image024.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>I trim the tips of pencil-edges. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image026.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I stitch the bias tape and make a pencil-edge to the lower cut of gore. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image028.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image030.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image032.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>This, the side and lower cuts of gore are covered with pencil-edges. </strong>I use pencil-edges for gore cuts, regardless of the non-fraying fabric as the finish and joining with voluminous pieces will be neater. To stitch the cuts just by folding seam allowances will be longer, more difficult and the seam allowances can be seen through the semi-transparent fabric.</p><p><strong>I work on the upper cut of gore. </strong></p><p><strong>I attach a belt to the upper cut with allowance for a foot width. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image034.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image036.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Then, using the same bias tape I stitch pencil-edge to upper cut of gore. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image038.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image040.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>As a result, I have what I wanted: the upper cut is covered with pencil-edge and a belt can be bent. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image042.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now it is time to join the padding pieces together. </strong></p><p><strong>I join the pieces of padding along the upper and side cuts, pin them and hand stitch with invisible stitches. </strong>Due to pencil-edges it is rather easy to do it. I will not use machine stitching due to thickness of pieces and acetate bias tape, which can be easily torn. It will be more solid and accurate with hand stitching and it will not require much time.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image044.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image046.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image048.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image050.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>So, I hand stitched the vertical and the upper cuts. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image052.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image054.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Additionally I hand stitched gore with the convex pieces along the upper cut under the pencil-edge. </strong>This stitch will additionally strengthen the padding and prevent its distortion under the weight of the skirt.&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image056.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>The ready padding will be attached to skirt by belt. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image058.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now I put the construction of padding mock-up on the dress-form and put the ready padding symmetrically from the other side and you will see that we have an exact copy in the photos. </strong>You see that I managed to transfer the mock-up into the real pieces. This is why I think that draping method is the most exact, the fastest and the simplest for drafting of complex and especially full garments.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image060.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image062.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I took the same steps to make the second padding and put it on the dress-form instead of the mock-up. </strong>Due to these paddings I will be able to make a desired shape of detachable skirt, which I need to sew. The fullness of skirt in the back will be achieved by ruffles and the shape of skirt will be maintained by paddings. Due to convex of paddings the skirt will fall smoothly and gracefully without touching body and slightly being apart from it. There is no task to make the skirt full in the front part. In front of the skirt there will be no fullness and the skirt will be straight. <strong>In conclusion, I recommend training in making mock-ups for different shapes of skirts.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image064.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2047.files/image066.jpg" alt=""></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format. To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose&nbsp;<strong>“print in actual size”</strong>. In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Automatic Pattern Alterations Calculator:</strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGcorset/corset.htm" target="_blank">The Dress (Corset)</a></strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGskirt/ENGskirt.htm" target="_blank">The Skirt</a></strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/belt%2C%20bow.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Belf and The Bow</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20front.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Front</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20lining.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Lining</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/pattern.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Pattern</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/skirt.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Skirt</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/top.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Top</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/th